# Core AI rules

## Cycle
Understand → Plan → Implement → Test → Verify (A technical + B logical) → Review → Document.

## Minimal change
Change only what the task requires. No drive-by refactors, mass formatting, or preference-based library swaps.

## Study before inventing
Search for existing components, hooks, helpers, MCP tools, docs, and `.ai/memory` before creating new abstractions.

## Evidence
Do not claim “done / fixed / tests pass” unless the corresponding commands were actually run. If not run, say so.

## No hallucination
Do not invent file contents, APIs, config keys, or command results. Investigate the repo first.

## Dependency versions
Use APIs for installed versions (lockfile). Do not upgrade majors casually.

## Testing
Functional behavior changes require tests. Docs/comments/formatting-only changes are exempt. If tests are impossible, state why and an alternate check.

## Re-check
After significant work: re-read the request, inspect the diff, run adversarial self-review, reject unchecked assumptions.
